Package model

Holds all the data structures and methods provided for the Parking lot and User Data classes

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ParkingSpaceInterface
    This is the interface that ParkingLot implements Honestly don't think this was necessary, but oh well
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CashRegister
    CashRegister is coordinates the interaction between the garage and the point of sale.
    Garage
    The Garage class takes in the parking lot and user data manager objects.
    ParkingLot
    This is the parking lot "bag" that contains the spaces
    Space
    Space's whole purpose is store a lot of the data on the car as well as the values that have been selected at the time of check in.
    Ticket
    The ticket class is used to close and format a nice string that'll be used to help inform the driver of their charge and be logged in the data to be viewed
    UserData
    UserData is an object for each Parking Attendant employee and Admin Automatically creates a default admin account if the UserDataManager passes in a zero
    UserDataManager
    User Data manager is a container for the employee data, including first and last name, usernames, passwords User data is stored in an array list with index 0 being an admin by default
    Vehicle
    The Vehicle class provides the makeup of info needed for a vehicle
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    State
    This holds the enum State since there is a limited amount of state's to register in
    VehicleType
    VehicleType enum to restrict values Possibilities are VehicleType.TRUCK, VehicleType.CAR, VehicleType.MOTORCYCLE
